FBIS4-57738 "drlat100_i_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-100 Daily Report 23 May 1994 Nicaragua Daniel Ortega Reelected FSLN Secretary General Daniel Ortega Reelected FSLN Secretary General PA2305154094 Paris AFP in Spanish 1456 GMT 23 May 94 PA2305154094 Paris AFP Spanish BFN [Text] Managua, 23 May (AFP) -- Official sources have reported that today, at the conclusion of the Sandinist National Liberation Front [FSLN] Special Congress, former Nicaraguan President Daniel Ortega was reelected secretary general of his party for a new three-year period. Ortega was able to secure the support of the majority of the "orthodox" sector of the FSLN for his proposal to maintain the party's traditional struggle politicies in opposition to the current endorsed by his election adversary, Henry Ruiz, a legendary Sandinist leader who represented the reformist sector of this political organization.
